==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tombac
<hw>Tom"bac</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pg.
<ets>tambaca</ets>,<ets>tambaque</ets>, fr. Malay
<ets>tamb⟦amac⟧ga</ets> copper; cf. Skr. <ets>t⟦amac⟧mraka</ets>; cf. F.
<ets>tombac</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Metal.)</fld> <def>An alloy of copper
and zinc, resembling brass, and containing about 84 per cent of copper;
-- called also <altname>German brass</altname> <it>or</it>
<altname>Dutch brass</altname>. It is very malleable and ductile, and
when beaten into thin leaves is sometimes called <altname>Dutch
metal</altname>. The addition of arsenic makes <stype>white
tombac</stype>.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>tombak</asp>, and
<asp>tambac</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tombester</ent>⟦br⟧
